title: Expose structural GraphQL types
body:
The types that were moved to the top level export in this change are fundamental to the way GraphQL objects are defined, especially when it comes to generating them. When `GraphQLInputType` of `GraphQLObjectFieldConfig` are the return type of functions they should definitely be exported.

In PostGraphQL we have been [rolling our own types](https://github.com/calebmer/postgraphql/blob/5a5ad3aa540d05da659df26e6fd744dd1800895d/typings/graphql.d.ts) for the `graphql` module. Wed like to use the definitions published under the `@types` namespace if possible. These changes are required to make that migration.

title: Rewrite WebRTC RTCPeerConnection definitions
body:
The WebRTC specification moves fast, and these definitions were very outdated. They also relied on enums sometimes because at the time of writing string union types (`type foo = 'a' | 'b'`) didn't exist yet. There was also a lot of deprecated API still present.

I used the [specification](https://www.w3.org/TR/webrtc/) IDL to rewrite all definitions in `RTCPeerConnection.d.ts`.

In the end I had to comment out some of the attributes because they clashed with types defined in `lib.es6.d.ts`. Not sure what the best approach would be here.

I also removed vendor specific prefixes. I think the correct approach when doing WebRTC is to use [adapter.js](https://github.com/webrtc/adapter). Otherwise people can add their own vendor-prefixed definitions if they wish.

Legacy API (with callbacks instead of promises) is not (yet) implemented. Does someone think this is important?

@groege @vvkame @martinduparc @bemasc @nakakura @iislucas @nestalk @smithkl42

title: Rewrite WebRTC RTCPeerConnection definitions
body:
The WebRTC specification moves fast, and these definitions were very outdated. They also relied on enums sometimes because at the time of writing string union types (`type foo = 'a' | 'b'`) didn't exist yet. There was also a lot of deprecated API still present.

I used the [specification](https://www.w3.org/TR/webrtc/) IDL to rewrite all definitions in `RTCPeerConnection.d.ts`.

In the end I had to comment out some of the attributes because they clashed with types defined in `lib.es6.d.ts`. Not sure what the best approach would be here.

I also removed vendor specific prefixes. I think the correct approach when doing WebRTC is to use [adapter.js](https://github.com/webrtc/adapter). Otherwise people can add their own vendor-prefixed definitions if they wish.

Legacy API (with callbacks instead of promises) is not (yet) implemented. Does someone think this is important?

@groege @vvkame @martinduparc @bemasc @nakakura @iislucas @nestalk @smithkl42

---

title: Fix ng file upload progress event
body:
`ng-file-upload` has a `progress(callback)` method that can be used to listen for progress events for in-progress uploads. The callback is called with a wrapped version of [ProgressEvent](https://developer.mozilla.org/en/docs/Web/API/ProgressEvent).

The definitions for `progress(callback)` method had the wrong type for its callback. It should be `IFileProgressEvent`, not `IHttpPromiseCallback<T>`. The latter makes no sense  the result of the upload is not known until it has been completed.
